n of usage of expensive options for a category of items to understand the
 how much status the representative consumer may derive with the choice
 for expensive items in a category.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Given our earlier discussion on scarcity, a clarification must be made about
 consumption item's rareness - which in itself does not imply scarcity of
 the item.
 For example, maternity products or musical instruments would always be
 limited to a certain section of the population - but they become a status
