\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We assume that a consumer establishes the preference of categories for status
 consumption over a longer period of time.
 The consumer may still decide to spend more on food if she couldn't find
 a way to differentiate status in housing, but whether the degree to how
 much she would spend is fixed over time.
 This is aligned with the literature on visible consumption 
